We need to define why the current feature set is important now more than
ever, yes, BUT we also ultimately need to be able to distinguish ourselves
from the competition separate from remote work.

A few notes:


   - Quantitative (because without face to face contact it is impossible to
   aggregate qualitative assessments up through the management chain)

Yes, AND quantitative data lets you multivariate test means of changing
behaviors/beliefs - otherwise you have to just "shout at the crowd."


   - Promote autonomous working and decision making, because your workers
   are newly autonomous (therefore employees need to be seeing their part i=
n /
   contribution to the cultural data that you are looking at)

Yes, AND otherwise you have more conduct risk, IP theft potential, and
off-brand PR damage potential than ever before.


   - Avoid building a commodity employee (messaging, training and learning
   needs to be framed in relation to target corporate culture)

Yes, mostly because it'll reduce churn. We already know that loss of top
talent is a major cost for employers. Now that everyone is virtual there is
less than ever keeping employees from just spending time sending out
resume's.


   - Build a method of managing culture that helps you in the future,
   emerge stronger from the crisis

How? Think we need to really nail this one down. What kind of future are we
looking to help companies build?


- J

